Xbox 360 is ready for tomorrow with a leaner look and a sleek black finish. With built-in wi-fi, you can connect instantly to the world of entertainment on Xbox LIVE, where HD movies and TV stream in an instant. It's ready for the controller-free experiences of Kinect, where you don't just play the game, you are the game. The huge hard drive has plenty of space to store your favorite games and movies. Xbox 360 E Console with 250GB Hard Drive 
 
The new console is sleeker and quieter with a stylish design that will be the centerpiece of your home entertainment system. The internal 250GB hard drive allows you to save your games and store television shows, movies, music, pictures, trailers, levels, demos and more extras available from Xbox LIVE Marketplace.

Built in Wi-Fi

Xbox 360 Wireless Controller 
 
This award-winning, high-performance wireless controller features the Xbox Guide Button for quick, in-game access to friends and music. It has a range of up to 30 feet and a battery life of 30 hours on two AA batteries.

I have the original purchase receipt and the console is eligible for warranty registration through Microsoft. It also comes with a bonus white wireless controller so two controllers total.

description:
Game is in good condition, no scratches. Pick up and cash only 

As it's small I will also accept payment via paypal and ship the game to you. To cover paypal and postage costs please add $4 and let me know when you respond so that I can send a payment request. I'll also need your shipping address too. Thanks 
 
 
 
Set in the science fiction realms of the film franchise crossover, Aliens vs. Predator is a high-definition action-adventure composed of tense, violent, kill-or-be-killed scenarios. Following the design concept of earlier AvP shooters, the game pits three different factions against one another. Players take the roles of deadly xenomorph aliens, stealthy predators, and heavily armed space marines, to do battle with enemies from the other two factions. Evolved to protect the brood, the alien xenomorphs are unmatched in melee combat, and excel at surprise attacks with their overpowering strength. Born of a species of hunters, the predator is a master of well-timed assaults and agile attacks. Physically weak but at a technological advantage, the human marines use heavy firepower to take down enemies from a distance. In many of the game's levels, warriors from all three factions must fight against one another in the same battles, at the same time. 
 
Great video game.

title: Destiny The Taken King For Xbox One Legendary Edition Used Owned by Adult
description:
Product Information 
The third expansion for Bungie's popular shared-world FPS, The Taken King introduces a new enemy class and a new story campaign. The action centers on Oryx, who leads the new Taken race on a quest to destroy the Guardians and avenge the death of his son Crota. Players must make their way onto Oryx's massive Hive Dreadnaught ship, use new abilities, weapons, and gear to defeat his corrupted army, and eventually bring down the Taken King. This Legendary Edition includes the full original game, The Taken King expansion, and all other previously released DLC. 
 
The action once again finds gamers serving as a Guardian, exploring long-lost civilizations on Earth and its closest neighbors. Players can create and customize their Guardian, choosing from the cyborg Exo, ethereal Awoken, and Human species, and then selecting from the Hunter, Warlock, and Titan classes. The Taken King introduces three new subclasses, with Warlocks harnessing electricity, Hunters using a bow made of gravitational void energy, and Titans wielding a flaming hammer. This expansion increases the level cap to 40, includes new Crucible PvP maps, new co-op Strike missions, and a new six-player Raid, and the friendly robot companion Ghost returns, though with the voice of Nolan North instead of Peter Dinklage.

title: Fallout 4 w/ Poster For Xbox One Standard Factory Edition Used Owned by Adult
description:
Detailed item info 
Product Information 
Bethesda Softworks' post-apocalyptic open-world RPG returns with a new setting, an enhanced crafting system, and thousands of lines of dialogue in Fallout 4. The action takes place in and around Boston roughly 200 years after a nuclear holocaust, with gamers assuming the role of the last survivor of a large fallout shelter known as Vault 111. Upon emerging from their shelter, players confront a devastated landscape where various factions battle for control of small settlements, and the wilderness teems with dangerous creatures, violent robots, mutated monsters, and deadly radiation. 
 
Gamers begin by creating their character, choosing from either a male or female vault survivor, and then customizing seven different S.P.E.C.I.A.L. skills. They are then free to roam the entire landscape as they please, meeting a variety of interesting characters, completing tasks, collecting bottle caps as currency, and acquiring useful items and weapons. Players can choose to interact with the world from a first- or third-person perspective, and combat once again mixes real-time action with turn-based elements in the form of the V.A.T.S. system, which lets gamers use action points to slow time and target specific areas of a foe's body. Fallout 4 introduces the ability to automatically perform critical hits, followed by a cooldown period, and for the first time in a Bethesda game, the player character can speak. Gamers can also collect materials to build their own settlements, complete with water, electricity, vegetation, outside vendors, and security measures.

title: Harmony Universal Remote for Xbox
description:
Logitech's Harmony Universal Remote control for Xbox 360,  model:  
  
 
 
This device is discontinued and is now a rare find, selling for almost $200 on Amazon and over $250 on eBay! It's a universal remote control designed to work great with your Xbox 360 (navigate Xbox menus with X, Y, A and B buttons). Of course, it control all your other entertainment devices, too (you can add up to 11 other components). I upgraded to a new remote since I don't use my Xbox 360 anymore, but this remote works great.  
 
Requires someone who knows their AV system to set it up. Once set up, you're whole family can use it easily. My family loves it since it simplifies our home entertainment system (AV receiver, TV, and 4-5 other devices)... Press one button (Watch TV, Play Xbox, Watch Bluray, etc.) and the remote takes care of turning on all the right devices and setting the right inputs. Press one button to turn it all off. Truly easy.

title: Xbox 360 and awesome games
description:
250 GB Xbox 360 and two controllers. 
 
You'll also get the following (amazing) games: 
 
Dragon Age: Inquisition 
Skyrim 
Red Dead Redemption 
Halo 4 
Batman Arkham Asylum 
Batman Arkham City 
Batman Arkham Origins 
FIFA '12 
Fable III ... just because. 
 
Except for maybe Mass Effect 2, those are the only games you really need if you, like me, enjoy single-player adventures. 
 
The Xbox runs like a champ and also plays DVDs -- I haven't had a problem with it yet. 
 
Price is firm, but I won't be a dick and keep your money if it breaks down in the first month or something. 
 
Oh yeah, and you'll inherit Loki the Dark Elf in Skyrim; he's a master (almost) of Illusion Magic and Sneak and a member of the Nightengales (aka an elite member of the Thieves Guild). He moves swiftly and stealthily about through the shadows of Tamriel, playing with the minds of the peasants. Sometimes he calms those who panic when they wake up and find him stealing their Void Salts in the dead of night. Other times he sends unsuspecting tribes of Forsworn into a curious frenzy of self-mutilation. Sometimes when facing undead, Loki himself goes up in flames. He remains unharmed while all those who venture within the boundaries of his fire do not. They all turn to ash. All the while, Loki keeps to the shadows and quietly directs the fate of Tamriel, pulling the strings of the townsfolk, all of whom are his puppets. 
... 
In sum, Loki is a badass and he still has a lot of room to develop if you enjoy playing as him. He's only like, level 22, but his Sneak and Illusion stats are around 70. 
 
But you can buy this XBox and trash Loki, too, obviously. That's also an option.

title: Call of Duty Black Ops III Standard Factory Edition Used Owned by Adult
description:
Product Information 
Activision's best-selling first-person shooter returns with a four-player co-op campaign, expanded multiplayer options, and more zombie-blasting action in Call of Duty: Black Ops III. The story is set in the year 2065, when air defense systems have grown so advanced that most combat involves robotic humanoids battling behind enemy lines. Gamers take control of a group of supersoldiers as they make their way through expansive levels designed to accommodate four players. Each character can be fully customized, and gamers can collect tokens to acquire new weapons and unlock new gear. 
 
The competitive multiplayer modes now feature a new momentum-based movement system designed to create more fluid action, with gamers using thrust jumps, wall runs, and slides, while still maintaining the ability to fire their weapons. A new Specialist character system lets players pick from a handful of unique soldiers, master their weapons and abilities, and rank them up, while the new Gunsmith feature offers hundreds of ways to customize weapons. Black Ops III also marks the return of Treyarch's signature zombie gameplay, with the new Shadows of Evil mode offering a film-noir experience set in the 1940s fictional town of Morg City. Gamers choose from four troubled and amnesia-stricken protagonists, and then guide them through multiple districts, earning XP along the way.

title: RARE PS2 Gamester FPS Master programmable controller by Radica "Scuf"
description:
This is a rare and interesting 3rd party controller for the Playstation 2 that has a cult following. This is designed around first person shooters, optimizing button layout to keep your thumbs on the analog sticks as much as possible. The controller will work with any PS2 game, but you wouldn't want to use them for racing games. 
 
The grips are styled after pistols, and the triggers are more abrupt than the long throw, heavy sprung triggers on the Xbox 360 for example. That means less fatigue in shooter games where you pull a trigger rapidly. The Radica Gamester FPS Master has 2 long, curved grips that feature rubber texturing front and back. The trigger is surrounded by a guard, just like a real gun. 
 
On top, the dual analog sticks are placed in a natural, neutral position. The grip design places your thumbs in line with the sticks. You don't have to reach for them. The left side features the D-pad and the start and select buttons, while the circle and square buttons are located below the right stick. 
 
On the inside edge of the grips there are 2 buttons on each side that fall under your middle and ring fingers. These are L1 and R1 along with 'X' and Triangle. This was a revolutionary design for the time. It does a lot of the things high end and modified controllers like Scuf and the Xbox One Elite controller offer these days. 
 
In the middle of the controller is a small backlit LCD screen and 6 buttons that let you remap the buttons and save 3 different configurations. If you don't like the default button assignments, you can change them, you'll just have to remember what each button is vs what symbol is marked on the body of the controller. This is built into the controller itself and is totally  independent of the Playstation 2. 
 
I am downsizing my collection of video games and controllers. This is a great piece of VG history, and actually very comfortable to hold in my opinion. This would make a great gift as a collectible or to open and use. The build quality is not Sony / Microsoft or Nintendo level however.

title: The  Torch wifi "nanny"
description:
Not sure how to describe this so I call it a "wifi interrupter". It's similar to the Circle by Disney and is a device you attach to your modem that enables you, very easily from an app on your phone, to control the wifi going to each and every device you set up.  You can block specific sites, genres of sites (i.e. gambling, online games) or flat out shut off wifi to a particular device without shutting down your ipad in the process. 
 
Kid on Xbox Live too much? Shut it down or set specific time limits for Xbox without having to pull the wifi plug on every other device in the house (who hasn't changed the wifi password or unplugged wifi out of frustration then had to go back and log in each. and. every. device. again.?) 
 
Want to block homework kids from games and social media during homework time but not shut the toddler off from the ipad? With Torch you can set up profiles for, and control, each device individually. Or, want to shut everyone off during dinner? You can do that with one tap, all at once. 
 
My own two cents is this it worth it for the arguments it stops; the whining that goes along with "turn off Minecraft, NOW". It just shuts them down when the specified time comes.  Furthermore, you'll never giggle more than when you say to your kids "if you hit your brother one more time and I'm turning off your wifi", and then...you touch a button on the app and BOOM, no more wifi!  
 
So...if it's so great, why am I getting rid of it? Well..... 
 
I bought this during a Kickstarter campaign almost 2 years ago but it took longer to ship than expected so I broke down and bought the Circle instead. Now I don't need the Torch, though I think it's probably more robust than Circle. I just don't have the patience to get used to a new platform, even though setup for both is easy-peasy. 
 
Visit mytorch.com to learn more about the setup and check the pics to see what it looks like and some of the features.

Product Description 
 
Three Highly Capable Audio Products in One 'PX' stands for 'Power experience.' That's because the DACmini PX adds a power amplifier to CEntrance's popular and award-winning DACmini CX. The DACmini PX consists of, in fact, three highly capable audio products in one. It's a DAC, a headphone amp, and a power amp all packaged in a compact, machined aluminum chassis that looks great on a desk or shelf. A Versatile Audio Hub The DACmini PX is designed to be the centerpiece of your computer audio system. It returns the warmth to your digital audio without being obtrusive. As a mini system with elevated sound quality, DACmini PX offers hours of fatigue-free listening enjoyment. Satisfied owners praise the sound for having "transparent highs, tight bass, and clarity in the mid-range only found in products well above the $1,000 price range." The DACmini PX features 24-bit, 192 kHz performance over SPDIF and 24-bit, 96 kHz over USB. It produces virtually unmeasurable jitter for amazing clarity and definition, and it offers exceptional noise immunity via a galvanically-isolated design. It boasts an analog input, headphone output, and line-level output. It easily streams music from such sources as a Mac or Windows computer, music server, iPod/iPhone, Apple TV, Airport Express, Xbox 360, PlayStation 3, and Squeezebox. 'Class A' Headphone Stage The DACmini PX has a superb sounding 'Class A' headphone stage that can drive virtually any headphones with very low distortion. The headphone stage has no capacitors in the signal path and offers clarity, a large soundstage, and freedom from listening fatigue. The power amplifier with beautiful 25-watt-per-channel power output uses a design that is based on the next-generation 'Class D' technology. It easily drives the majority of bookshelf speakers. Placed near your computer monitor, the DACmini PX becomes the core of a very powerful and versatile desktop audio setup.

title: Kinivo HDMI Switch 301BN
description:
Kinivo HDMI Switch 301BN Premium 3 Port Wireless Remote & AC Power Adapter 
 
Switches 3 high speed HDMI inputs into one output. Includes AC power adapter. 
Can switch automatically (based on active input) 
Supports manual switching using the supplied IR wireless remote or the button on the device 
Supports 3D and HD resolutions unto 1080p 
 
Description: 
Kimiko 301BN is a premium quality high Speed HDMI switch for your gaming or home theater setup. It allows for switching up to 3 HDMI inputs into one output and supports resolutions up to 1080p. Easy plug & play operation simply plug in the HDMI input sources into the input connections and the output connection to your TV or projector. 301BN will automatically switch to the currently active input source if there is only one active input. If there are multiple active inputs, then you can select the input either using the IR remote or using the select button on the switch. The HDMI signal from the selected input is passed through to the output HDMI connection. Quality picture and sound - Automating switching function), IR remote controlled switching or manual switching - AC powered (power adapter included) for maximum compatibility - supports 3D, HDCP and all other HDMI 1.3 Features - guaranteed 1080p, 1080I, 720p, 480p, and 480I resolutions - Works with all HDTVs, Blu-ray players, Xbox 360, PS3 and other HDMI devices - helps reduce clutter of HDMI wires being fed into your HDTV note: Apple TV keeps its HDMI port active even in the sleep state. Hence, Auto-switching may not work with the Apple TV. Manual switching can still be used in this scenario.  
 
Contents: 
301BN HDMI switch  
IR remote control with battery  
AC power adapter 
 
Condition: Excellent, like-new 
Comes from a pet and smoke free home.

title: Xbox 360 Limited Edition Kinect Star Wars Bundle by Microsoft
description:
If you can see this ad, it's available. 
 
Price is firm 
 
Stock photos. Local transaction only, cash only, no PayPal, no shipping.  If you're serious leave me your phone number so I can call or text you.  We can meet in safe public place between Mountain View and Fremont. 
 
Used very little, excellent conditions.  We still have all the items below including the original box. 
Xbox 360 Console: Bring the Star Wars characters you know and love into your living room with this custom R2-D2-themed Xbox 360 console with custom sounds. 
Kinect Sensor: Includes the first ever custom white sensor. Immerse yourself into the Star Wars universe with full-body gameplay. 
Xbox 360 Wireless Controller: Includes custom C-3PO-themed Xbox 360 Wireless Controller. 
Kinect Star Wars game: Enter the Star Wars universe like never before. Use the Force like a Jedi, become a champion Pod Racer, pilot iconic ships and much more. 
Kinect Adventures game: Get off the couch and into the game in a whole new way. You and your friends and family will jump, dodge, and kick your way through 20 pulse-pounding adventures set in exotic locations. 
320GB Hard Drive: The largest hard drive available on Xbox 360. 
 
Product Description 
Get the Xbox 360 Limited Edition Kinect Star Wars bundle, with the first ever white Kinect Sensor and custom-designed console and controller based on popular Star Wars characters R2-D2 and C-3PO. Use the Force like a Jedi and immerse yourself in the Star Wars experience you've always dreamed of, in ways you never imagined possible. 
 
From the Manufacturer 
Get the Xbox 360 Limited Edition Kinect Star Wars bundle, with the first ever white Kinect Sensor and custom-designed console and controller based on popular Star Wars characters R2-D2 and C-3PO. Use the Force like a Jedi and immerse yourself in the Star Wars experience you've always dreamed of, in ways you never imagined possible. 
 
Kinect Star Wars game (included) 
Feel the Force. You are the Controller. "Kinect Star Wars" brings Star Wars to life like never before. Harnessing the controller-free power of Kinect for Xbox 360, "Kinect Star Wars" allows fans to physically hone their Jedi skills, wield the power of the Force in their hands, pilot iconic ships and vehicles, rampage as a vicious Rancor monster or even dance with iconic Star Wars characters. Using full body motions, players can live out the ultimate Star Wars fantasy to use the Force, battle with a Lightsaber and more -- no controller required. 
 
Enter the Galaxy. True to the Star Wars you know and love, "Kinect Star Wars" brings to life the "galaxy far, far away" with stunning visuals, complete with iconic characters, vehicles, ships, Droids and much more. 
Use the Force. Drawing on iconic moments from the entire saga, "Kinect Star Wars" invites you to experience a wide variety of physical play, including harnessing the powers of the Jedi Knights with your fingertips. 
Customize your training. Experience the breadth of the Star Wars Universe as you wield a Lightsaber, train to be a Jedi Master, soar in command of a speeder bike, become a champion Podracer, wreak havoc as a rampaging Rancor, battle the Dark Side in one-on-one duels, dance for Jabba the Hutt, and much more. 
Join forces. Share the Force with friends through co-op, competitive and duel modes. Easy jump-in and out lets a second player join in instantly on the Jedi action.

title: Xbox 360 Slim 4GB Used, 8GB USB Stick, 1 Controller w/ Charge Station
description:
DESCRIPTION: 
 
This Xbox 360 gave me many hours of fun for about 5 years. It's a great way to connect to media over the internet or enjoy a vast library of Xbox 360 games! 
 
The 4 GB onboard memory can be consumed quickly if you are playing a lot of games, so please enjoy a bonus 8 GB Xbox 360 branded memory stick to ensure you have the storage to get your game on. 
 
Nyko Controller charging station ensures your controller is always charged. Just install the included battery pack and leave the controller in the stand to charge. 
 
CONDITION: 
 
Used for 5 years moderately for gaming and constantly for media streaming. Good cosmetic condition and working order. Never experienced any issues that were not solved by rebooting. 
 
INCLUDES: 
 
Console and Storage 
1 - Xbox 360 Slim Console with 4 GB internal Hard Drive 
1 - BONUS 8 GB Xbox 360 branded memory stick 
1 - Power Unit and Power Cables 
1 - HDMI cable 
1 - Audio Adapter for use with RCA A/V cable (use this to connect audio with red & white cables) 
 
Controllers and Controller Charger 
1 - Black & Grey Controller 
1 - Black Controller (Broken and not pictured. Cracked casing could be repaired.) 
1 - Nyko Controller Charging Station 
2 - Nyko Rechargeable Battery Packs 
 
SETUP: 
 
Everything is included here to start enjoying the Xbox 360 right away with HDMI or RCA A/V (red & white) cables for audio. Optical audio cable is not included. The HDMI cable will send audio signal to your TV or other device. Many audio systems can do a "pass-through" to your TV to allow for only HDMI output from the Xbox 360 The other audio option is to use the included audio converter and cable which will allow you to connect to a separate audio system or sound bar with Left/Right audio while using HDMI to connect to your TV.
